http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Tue 7 Mar 2017
Source: OIE, WAHID [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=23144


Foot and mouth disease, South Africa
------------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 7 Mar 2017 from Dr Bothle Michael Modisane, chief director, Department of Agriculture, Forestry and Fisheries, Animal Production and Health, Pretoria, South Africa

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 1 Mar 2017
Date of confirmation of the event: 3 Mar 2017
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: February 2016
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: foot and mouth disease [FMD] virus
Serotype: pending
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1 (FMD-2017-001): FMD_MPU_2017_001, Bushbuckridge, Mpumalanga
Date of start of the outbreak: 1 Mar 2017
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Total animals affected
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 1500 / 12 / 0 / 0 / 0
Affected population: Dairy project.
Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 0.8 / 0 / 0 / 0
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: this outbreak is located in South Africa's FMD Protection Zone, which is not part of the FMD Free Zone and, therefore, does not affect South Africa's OIE recognized FMD free status.

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country, screening, traceability, quarantine, surveillance within containment and/or protection zone, vaccination prohibited, no treatment of affected animals.
Measures to be applied: no other measures.

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Agricultural Research Council - Onderstepoort Veterinary Institute (ARC - OVI) (OIE Reference Laboratory) / Cattle / liquid-phase blocking ELISA / 3 Mar 2017 / Positive
Agricultural Research Council - Onderstepoort Veterinary Institute (ARC - OVI) (OIE Reference Laboratory) / Cattle / polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 3 Mar 2017 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Since August 2015 to Feb 2016, South Africa reported to the OIE 6 outbreaks of foot and mouth disease (FMD) caused by FMDV SAT 3 strain in Limpopo province. The event was resolved on 22 Apr 2016. See report and map at http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review/viewsummary?reportid=19321.

Since August 2013 to June 2014, South Africa reported to the OIE 13 outbreaks of FMD caused by FMDV SAT 2 strain in Mpumalanga province. The event was resolved on 10 Feb 2015. See report and map at http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/temp/reports/en_fup_0000017240_20150224_143809.pdf.

A map of the FMD free zone in South Africa can be seen at http://www.oie.int/fileadmin/Home/eng/Animal_Health_in_the_World/map/A_South%20Africa.jpg (last update May 2015). - Mod.CRD


A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4886253,179.]
